The paper focuses on cross-modal image retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. The use of subspace learning and graph embedding also suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper specifically mentions the use of Locally Linear Embedding, which is a common technique in computer vision research (cs.CV). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on three public datasets, which suggests a focus on multimedia (MM) research.
